verbs.description: increep (third-person singular simple present increeps, present participle increeping, simple past and past participle incrept)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, poetic) To creep in; to make a furtive entrance.
examples: First, order gone, and doores not being kept, / By baptisme heaps of prophane do rush. / With them, at length, a ministry incrept, / That with the horn God's ordinance did push.
